cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper is about wireless sensor networks (WSNs) and their optimization using clustering techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses energy efficiency, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The use of clustering for optimization suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of different clustering techniques, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
